==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Effeminately
<hw>Ef*fem"i*nate*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In an effeminate or womanish manner; weakly; softly;
delicately.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Proud and <xex>effeminately</xex> gay.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Fawkes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>By means of a woman; by the power or art of a
woman.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Effeminately</xex>
vanquished.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Effeminateness</ent>⟦br⟧
